                "id": "block-exeg-002",
                "orderNumber": 1,
                "title": "Psalm 23:1-6",
                "content": "1. The Lord is my shepherd, I will not be in need.\n2. He lets me lie down in green pastures; He leads me beside quiet waters.\n3. He restores my soul; He guides me in the paths of righteousness for the sake of His name.\n4. Even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I fear no evil, for You are with me; Your rod and Your staff, they comfort me.\n5. You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies; You have anointed my head with oil; my cup overflows.\n6. Certainly goodness and faithfulness will follow me all the days of my life, and my dwelling will be in the house of the Lord forever.",
                "isLocked": true,
                "contentFormat": "markdown",
                "exegesisHighlights": [
                  {
                    "id": "hl-004",
                    "orderNumber": 1,
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 51,
                    "noteMarkdown": "David doesn't say \"The Lord is **a** shepherd\" — he says \"**my** shepherd.\" This is personal. Do you know Him as YOUR shepherd, or just as a concept?"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "hl-005",
                    "orderNumber": 2,
                    "start": 199,
                    "end": 330,
                    "noteMarkdown": "Notice David doesn't say \"if\" but \"even though.\" The valley isn't hypothetical — it's guaranteed. But the promise isn't that you avoid it. The promise is that **He is with you** in it."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ],
